{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"40a321dc-12f8-4d49-8c08-e251bc415927","content":"Use **`dotnet run`**, not `dotnet test`.\n\nThe `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` package works with **Microsoft Testing Platform** (the newer runner), which is invoked via `dotnet run`. When you run:\n\n```\ndotnet run\n```\n\nthe test host starts, runs your tests, and then **stays alive** watching for file changes — rerunning affected tests on save.\n\n`dotnet test` uses the older VSTest adapter path, which doesn't support hot reload.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"288c1ace-5f6b-469d-9318-9820d5fe1f97","outputTokens":116,"requestId":"A02D:343F6:1A01DBE:1D7792A:69FE9121"},"id":"98a88a26-a4cc-4107-ac3e-838f570f26a4","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:43:02.510Z","parentId":"1b5abd0d-d727-4860-8254-cf892d75531f"}
